						               													<description>D-DAY SOLITAIRE is a fast-playing roll n' write dice game for one to five players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game attempts to recreate the Normandy landings of World War II in a simple yet challenging manner. The design is meant to be a quick, fun, and historical beer &amp;amp; pretzels simulation. There is a map sheet of varying difficulties for each of the five Normandy beaches -- Sword, Juno, Gold, Omaha, and Utah. You play as the Allied D-Day forces that hit the beaches on June 6th, 1944.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the multi-player variant, each player plays on one of the five beach maps against their own German A.I. opponent. The beach landings vary in difficulty; therefore, &amp;quot;extra points&amp;quot; are awarded based on the beach's level of difficulty in order to achieve a relative balance among all of the beaches. The player who achieves the highest score is declared the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;D-Day Solitaire is an entry in the 2022 Wargame Print and Play Game Design Contest&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Link to Work-in-Progress thread: [WIP] D-DAY SOLITAIRE (Contest Ready)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
